  </section>


  <section id="tracking" class="sg-content__group">
    <h2 class="t-heading -size-m">Google Analytics 'Page View' Tracking</h2>
    <p class="t-body">When a modal is opened with JavaScript, a pageview event is sent to Google Analytics to track modal usage. This will not happen when a modal is opened in a full page.</p>
    <p class="t-body">To track a modal as a pageview, append <code class="sg-code">data-google-analytics-page-title="..."</code> to the <code class="sg-code">.e-modal</code> element</p>

    <div class="sg-content__example">
      <%= code_example('markup') do %>
        <div class="e-modal" data-view="modalInternalControls" data-google-analytics-page-title="page_title_for_google-analytics_goes_here"></div>
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <br>
    <br>

    <h2 class="t-heading -size-s">Ignore pageview tracking for a modal</h2>
    <p class="t-body">In cases where it does not make sense to track the opening of a modal as a pageview (e.g an auto popup notification or a developer only tool), just do not include the <code class="sg-code">data-google-analytics-page-title</code> attribute.</p>
  </section>
</div>
